<subSubSection pageNumber="927" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="927">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="927">Note:</emphasis>
St John (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="927">Phytologia</emphasis>
33: 89-92. 1976) appeared to regard 852.3 (LINN) as the type but this sheet lacks the relevant 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="927">
<volumeTitle>Species Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
number (i.e. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“2”">&quot;2&quot;</normalizedToken>
) and was a post-1753 addition to the herbarium, and is not original material for the name. The same is true of 852.2 (LINN), treated as the type by Verdoorn (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="927">Bothalia</emphasis>
13: 275 1981), but not linked by Linnaeus with this name, and not original material for it.
</paragraph>
